
[1]profanation

   PROFANA'TION, n. [L. profano. See Profane.]

   1. The act of violating sacred things, or of treating them with
   contempt or irreverence; as the profanation of the sabbath by sports,
   amusements or unnecessary labor; the profanation of a sanctuary; the
   profanation of the name of God by swearing, jesting, &c.

   2. The act of treating with abuse or disrespect.

   'Twere profanation of our joys

   To tell the laity our love.
